The TEAM course is a course of the American Union of Surgeons which has developed from the ATLS (Advanced Trauma Life Support ) module and is adapted for medical students.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview about the standardised management of the trauma patient on the principles of Advanced Trauma Life Support for Doctors® (ATLS®) . The course includes primary management of the trauma patient, diagnostics of severe injuries, primary treatment of life-threatening injuries, stabilisation of the patient and his/her preparation for transportation to a higher level medical institution.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student - can describe prevention strategies of traumas and injuries; - can carry out a triage of the multitrauma patient; - can prioritize the stages of primary management of the multitrauma patient; - can describe the guidelines and methods to be used in primary stabilisation and final treatment of the multitrauma patient; - can identify how concomitant conditions, diseases and the mechanism of trauma influence primary treatment; - can describe and practise teamwork oriented management of the multritrauma patient at the primary level;   - can plan transportation of the trauma patient for definitive treatment at a higher level hospital
